There was a shop in Canada during the 70's, (don't know if it exists
anymore), that used to do that with the 40hp blocks. It was quite the
business for formula Vee racers when 40hp blocks were becoming rare and
formula Vee were restricted to that size engine. They exported a lot of
blocks to Europe and Australia for formula Vee also. There is steel stamp in
the case on the front side of the bell housing. You can tell these blocks
when apart by all the welding in the main ribs and around #3 oil path in the
bell housing. If you come across any, please take some pictures for the
website.

67 Single Cab, DP 1641cc 34PICT
71 Trike 1776cc 32/36 Progressive
VolksAir 1585cc 28 PICT
Ray, Kent WA
